        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 3:44PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 343 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Antelope, or 24 miles west of Fossil, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Antelope and Shaniko.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
